,1,1,1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Deontology is very different from consequentialism. While consequentialism consider an action is morally right action based on the consequence, deotology consider if an action is identified right and deontology has it's set moral rules. Therefore, based on deontology, even if an action brings the best consequence, if the action itself is a morally wrong action it cannot be a right act. Then, who and how to decide wheather the action is right or wrong? Here comes the virtue ethics. Virtue ethics argues that a virtuous person will do a morally right action as a human.Thus, if an action that vituous person do is a right actions. Then, who and how to decide wheather the person is virtuous or not?","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1,"offset":2679},"end":{"line":32,"column":702,"offset":3380},"indent":[]}},{"type":"html","value":"<br/>","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":702,"offset":3380},"end":{"line":32,"column":707,"offset":3385},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1,"offset":2679},"end":{"line":32,"column":707,"offset":3385},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Based on Deontology and Virtue Ethics, here are some questions I want you to think about to find out if posting have comments are right or wrong: :","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1,"offset":3389},"end":{"line":34,"column":148,"offset":3536},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1,"offset":3389},"end":{"line":34,"column":148,"offset":3536},"indent":[]}},{"type":"blockquote","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"i. Is posting hate comment considered a morally right action?\n","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":2,"offset":3539},"end":{"line":36,"column":1,"offset":3602},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"html","value":"<br/>","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1,"offset":3602},"end":{"line":36,"column":6,"offset":3607},"indent":[]